Change mmap() flags MAP_SHARED to MAP_PRIVATE.  The pvfs file system
on intrepid has problems with MAP_SHARED and we only read the file,
we never try to write it back.

Symtab calls mmap() with PROT_READ and MAP_SHARED which doesn't really
make any sense.


diff -Naurb symtabAPI.orig/src/dyninst/common/src/MappedFile.C symtabAPI/src/dyninst/common/src/MappedFile.C
--- symtabAPI.orig/src/dyninst/common/src/MappedFile.C	2011-04-07 14:51:50.000000000 -0500
+++ symtabAPI/src/dyninst/common/src/MappedFile.C	2012-02-24 17:33:11.000000000 -0600
@@ -316,7 +316,7 @@
 #else
 
    int mmap_prot  = PROT_READ;
-   int mmap_flags = MAP_SHARED;
+   int mmap_flags = MAP_PRIVATE;
 
 #if defined(os_vxworks)   
    // VxWorks kernel modules have relocations which need to be
